dct_description_sm: Relief shown pictorially. State 1 lacking any imprint in cartouche at lower left and with French text on verso. From: Hondius. Nouvel Theatre du Monde, 1639, 1640, 1641, or 1642. Covers North America, Central America, and northern part of South America. Copy 1 black and white; copy 2 hand colored. 1 map: col.; 45 x 54 cm. This map is in the public domain. Please attribute access and use of this digitized map to the Stephen S. Clark Library, University of Michigan Library.
dct_creator_sm: Hondius, Hendrik, 1597-1651.,Dahl, James, former owner.,Hondius, Hendrik, 1597-1651. Nouvel Theatre du Monde.
